The paper discusses a natural language processing system that conducts deep understanding of human-written papers, creates new ideas, and incrementally generates key elements of a new paper. This suggests that the paper falls under the categories of natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the system uses memory-attention networks, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and semantic analysis (cs.SD).
